      "source_text": "Non-exempt employees are eligible for overtime pay at a rate of one and one-half (1.5) times their regular rate of pay for all hours worked in excess of forty (40) hours in a single workweek. To be eligible for overtime, an employee's employment_status must be active. Employees who are terminated, resigned, or laid off are not eligible for overtime compensation for the week during which the employment action occurs. Furthermore, employees are not eligible for overtime compensation if their pay type is salaried; only hourly employees qualify. Finally, only those employees whose classification is considered non-exempt are eligible for overtime under the guidelines of the Fair Labor Standards Act (FLSA).",
